                <td bgcolor="#5A71AD" valign="top"><font color="white" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/25/2003&nbsp;: 11:45:07 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> A variation on what Sthythys posted is to clear your current target, then just sit down .  This usually only works when everyone else is standing, but on a bad pull, most people immediately stand up so it works ok, though you'll get smacked around a bit.  <br /><br />Another thing to try is /assist pets that are offtanking adds.  Pets are cool, 90% of the time they will immediately back off something you mez (doesn't work with Root though).  <br /><br />This may sound a little obvious, but /assist is also great for getting to the center of confusing piles of combatants.  Targetting anything that is attacking something else will eventually always get you either the main mob (for slowing or nuking) or the person it is cracking away at (for Lifebonding if it will help).  <br /><br />If you /assist a mob and your own name comes up, you need to start over :P.</span></font></td>
